stylometry: Genetic algorithm is the conventional way of solving using survival of the fittest factors, mutations, and crossovers. Evolutionary solver is the premium solvers way interpreting genetic algorithms. Evolutionary solver uses genetic algorithms to find a "good" solution. It uses random numbers when finding a solution therefore two different runs can obtain different solutions. The positive factors of evolutionary solver is that if it is ran long enough it can solve any optimization problem the negative factor is that we never know how long to run it for - it could take forever; therefore we usually limit it to  2-5 minutes for example and then take away the best solution it finds. The advantage of these is on "non-smooth" problems for example - discounts and deciding on two or more items.
